column5: OK... found ya on page 2
HEY GUYS!! NICE FISH!!
Great report Roy.  And yet another awesome day with Lloyd.
You're lucky Drew...I'm usually in the appendix....not too far from the colon.

Thanks Radar for putting up the pics. Jose will be up soon too. Im happy you did not put any of those pics up lol bad hair day lol loosing your hat is never a good thing lol Again very nice to meet you and hope to see you again.
Great report Roy...Looks like a blast with a tasty result  Sooo tempted to take a charter trip out onto Lake O one of these days
You're the man Lloyd!  Great bunch of fish guys!
Good to see ya out and about catching fish Roy
Dang! A Kodak moment for sure!
Looks like a great day on the water with some tasty treats for your efforts! Cheers,
Very nice day & catches for all of you. Thanks for sharing.

I had a wonderful time Saturday with Lloyd (Fishhunter), Jose and Radar. Got down to the dock around 5:15 Saturday morning and Lloyd was just putting away the breakfast dishes. Jose and Radar showed up minutes later and we waited for a 4th guy. At 6 it was time to leave. Beautiful day though with lots of sun and a light breeze. Here are a few action and money shots of the guys... none of me in there...it turns out that you have to be on the OTHER side of the camera to be in the pic.            Here's a shot of captain Jose!    Cutest fish of the day.                    Mr. Machete man.    And here's the thank you shot.    I had a great time on the bay with you guys. Looking forward to doing it again, Lloyd.
nice day on the water roy nice eyes
Niiiiiice!!
wAS A BLAST HAVING YOU ALL OUT. TO BAD FOR THE GUY THAT DID NOT SHOW UP. HE MISSED A GREAT DAY!! THANKS ROY FOR THE CASE OF BROWN POPS LOL JUST WHAT THE DOCTOR ORDERED )
Super report hon, looks like you all had a great day and some laughs.  Some nice fish there, bet they were tasty!!  Joey

Roy, I was the forth guy suppose to join you guys, all pumped-up till Friday noon. And then crap hit the fan and I was running between walk-in clinic and emergency with my wife till early Sunday. Anyhow... I missed I guess one of the very best fishing opportunity with you and Lloyd. Good shooting btw!
Good to see your long drive paid off Roy and everybody had a great trip....gotta luv Quinte anytime of the year.  Sure gonna miss my annual trip next weekend.
Wow, excellent catch.  great pics
Great stuff Roy.  Nice walters!  Here's me with my sixteen foot boat and you guys fishing from a yacht.....lol.
looks like a great time with Lloyd as always  I can't wait to get a chance to fish with him again
Sorry to hear about that Dusky. I hope your wife is ok now.
Great Report! Good to see you out fishing for a change Roy.lol
Great stuff Roy!!!! Told you that you'd have a good time... how can't you with that NUT!
Who you calling a NUT LOL
you have to ask...????   LOL
WELL   I GUESS SINCE YOU WERE NOT WITH US, I GUESS THAT MAKES IT ME.
YOU BAD!!!!!
see you do understand...LOL
Nice trip all it looks like fish and fun was had.   Art

Here you go Roy! He really did catch fish.        Had a great time guys.  Excellent job Lloyd - worth every penny! (Didn't post any without your hat tho.)  Had to laugh at the heavy duty machete and then the finesse machette for filleting. But they worked well. First meal sure was tasty!
Yup Lloyd has more big  knives than a Benihana  and he's as good with them
Only guy I know that can precison fillet a 10" brookie with a 22 " knife !!
Looks like a great day on the water boys.
Holy Roy... I saw it was your report but then almost missed ya until the end. lol.  Good catch of eyes for all involved.
